90
00:04:40,180 --> 00:04:40,650
Gou.

91
00:04:40,770 --> 00:04:42,210
Sorry for being late.

92
00:04:44,210 --> 00:04:46,290
Thank you for attending
Jingmin's memorial service.

93
00:04:46,650 --> 00:04:47,700
My condolences.

94
00:04:48,330 --> 00:04:49,180
Sit down.

95
00:04:49,844 --> 00:04:51,222
You have to look after yourself.

96
00:04:51,650 --> 00:04:53,020
Don't grieve too much.

97
00:04:56,180 --> 00:04:58,140
Duole, give your grandpa some water.

98
00:04:58,450 --> 00:04:58,700
Okay.

99
00:04:59,820 --> 00:05:00,820
Grandpa, have some water.

100
00:05:01,260 --> 00:05:01,850
In-law,

101
00:05:02,844 --> 00:05:04,022
please look after yourself.

102
00:05:04,044 --> 00:05:04,820
Have a seat.

103
00:05:05,330 --> 00:05:05,770
Okay.

104
00:05:07,740 --> 00:05:08,260
Shen.

105
00:05:08,970 --> 00:05:10,260
Jingmin has left us.

106
00:05:10,644 --> 00:05:12,333
At least she's free from her suffering.

107
00:05:13,043 --> 00:05:14,203
Think on the bright side.

108
00:05:16,770 --> 00:05:18,140
Now that Jingmin is gone,

109
00:05:20,311 --> 00:05:21,530
I have no one to talk to.

110
00:05:23,210 --> 00:05:24,970
There's no one to nag me now.

111
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:28,530
That's why,

112
00:05:29,140 --> 00:05:29,620
Shen,

113
00:05:30,060 --> 00:05:30,740
we have

114
00:05:31,140 --> 00:05:31,970
to keep on living

115
00:05:32,444 --> 00:05:34,140
for Jingmin's sake
and our children's sake.

116
00:05:34,550 --> 00:05:35,090
That's right.

117
00:05:35,090 --> 00:05:36,530
We still have a long way to go.

118
00:05:36,530 --> 00:05:36,890
Yes.

119
00:05:37,290 --> 00:05:39,770
We have to live well.

120
00:05:39,933 --> 00:05:40,970
We have to look forward.

121
00:05:41,620 --> 00:05:41,970
Yes.

122
00:05:42,180 --> 00:05:42,500
Yes.

123
00:05:43,290 --> 00:05:43,940
Just like me.

124
00:05:44,111 --> 00:05:45,844
We should inherit
the past and forge ahead.

125
00:05:47,622 --> 00:05:49,140
Inherit the past and forge ahead?

126
00:05:49,644 --> 00:05:50,700
What do you mean by that?

127
00:05:51,260 --> 00:05:53,530
My in-law just passed away not long ago,

128
00:05:53,700 --> 00:05:55,410
- now, you want him to move on?
- Mom!

129
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:57,059
- Don't you have a conscience?
- Mom!

130
00:05:57,060 --> 00:05:57,620
Sister-in-law.

131
00:05:57,620 --> 00:05:58,529
Stop calling me that.

132
00:05:58,530 --> 00:05:59,260
- What?
- Madam.

133
00:05:59,260 --> 00:05:59,580
Mom!

134
00:05:59,580 --> 00:06:00,450
Who are you?

135
00:06:00,450 --> 00:06:01,309
Stop it!

136
00:06:01,310 --> 00:06:02,260
What do you mean by that?

137
00:06:02,260 --> 00:06:04,090
You're overthinking it.
That's not what I mean.

138
00:06:04,090 --> 00:06:04,650
Stop saying.

139
00:06:04,650 --> 00:06:05,090
Stop it!

140
00:06:05,090 --> 00:06:05,380
Mom!

141
00:06:05,850 --> 00:06:06,820
Stop talking!

142
00:06:06,820 --> 00:06:08,580
He told your father to forge ahead!

143
00:06:08,580 --> 00:06:09,260
Stop it!

144
00:06:09,530 --> 00:06:10,580
Stop it!

145
00:06:10,580 --> 00:06:11,180
Madam!

146
00:06:11,222 --> 00:06:12,490
Enough. Stop explaining yourself.

147
00:06:12,890 --> 00:06:13,770
Mr. Gou, I'm sorry.

148
00:06:15,700 --> 00:06:16,530
Are you okay?

149
00:06:17,090 --> 00:06:17,620
Do you need

150
00:06:18,210 --> 00:06:19,330
some heart relief pills?

151
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:20,060
I have some.

152
00:06:20,177 --> 00:06:20,933
No need for that.

153
00:06:21,140 --> 00:06:21,650
I'm fine.

154
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:22,620
I'm fine.

155
00:06:28,620 --> 00:06:29,060
Dad.

156
00:06:29,890 --> 00:06:30,940
It's almost time.

157
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:32,740
Let's head to the farewell hall.

158
00:06:34,620 --> 00:06:34,940
Dad.

159
00:06:35,970 --> 00:06:36,450
Let's go.

160
00:06:37,260 --> 00:06:37,740
Slowly.

161
00:06:37,890 --> 00:06:38,450
Slowly.

162
00:06:38,580 --> 00:06:38,850
Duole.

163
00:06:38,850 --> 00:06:39,620
Slowly.

164
00:06:39,644 --> 00:06:40,330
Help Grandpa out.

165
00:06:40,355 --> 00:06:41,311
Hurry. Support him.

166
00:06:46,210 --> 00:06:49,380
Recalling the past, raising nephews
and grandchildren with frugality,

167
00:06:49,740 --> 00:06:52,820
leaving behind a noble example.

168
00:06:55,180 --> 00:06:56,970
Behold a hall of filial children,

169
00:06:57,380 --> 00:07:00,290
mourning deeply,
yet the voice and presence are no more.

170
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:04,140
May such great virtue be passed down
to inspire future generations.

171
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:08,500
Dad, are you okay?

172
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:09,933
Whose phone is that? Switch it off!

173
00:07:10,410 --> 00:07:10,650
Mom.

174
00:07:10,844 --> 00:07:11,500
It's your phone.

175
00:07:11,533 --> 00:07:11,890
No...

176
00:07:13,580 --> 00:07:14,650
Give me your hand.

177
00:07:14,650 --> 00:07:15,380
Come on.

178
00:07:20,140 --> 00:07:20,410
Dad!

179
00:07:20,530 --> 00:07:20,850
Dad!

180
00:07:22,410 --> 00:07:22,940
Dad!

181
00:07:23,380 --> 00:07:24,060
In-law!

182
00:07:25,020 --> 00:07:25,410
Grandpa!

183
00:07:25,410 --> 00:07:25,820
In-law!

184
00:07:25,820 --> 00:07:26,210
Dad!

185
00:07:26,380 --> 00:07:26,850
In-law!

186
00:07:26,850 --> 00:07:28,155
Give him the heart relief pills!

187
00:07:28,530 --> 00:07:29,090
In-law!

188
00:07:30,140 --> 00:07:34,260
Call 120! We need urgent treatment!

189
00:07:35,780 --> 00:07:41,330
