190
00:07:55,580 --> 00:07:56,060
Dear.

191
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:57,180
Time to eat.

192
00:07:57,450 --> 00:07:57,890
Grandpa.

193
00:08:04,020 --> 00:08:04,330
Dad.

194
00:08:04,622 --> 00:08:05,955
Do you want some tofu pudding?

195
00:08:06,700 --> 00:08:07,180
No.

196
00:08:10,450 --> 00:08:12,820
Why don't you let me organize
Mom's belongings today?

197
00:08:13,530 --> 00:08:14,890
The Mid-Autumn Festival is nearing.

198
00:08:15,022 --> 00:08:16,990
Her coat is still hanging there,
collecting dust.

199
00:08:20,850 --> 00:08:21,450
Lina, come.

200
00:08:23,140 --> 00:08:24,290
Since Dad doesn't want that,

201
00:08:24,290 --> 00:08:25,490
you should stop bringing it up.

202
00:08:28,210 --> 00:08:29,700
Mom has passed away for a long time.

203
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:31,600
Look at how your father is acting.

204
00:08:33,930 --> 00:08:35,220
He's playing the music again.

205
00:08:35,355 --> 00:08:37,088
I don't even have the mood to eat now.

206
00:08:43,050 --> 00:08:43,460
Dad,

207
00:08:43,777 --> 00:08:45,360
I know you can't bear to part with her.

208
00:08:45,650 --> 00:08:46,620
But you'll feel better

209
00:08:46,620 --> 00:08:48,020
once her things are organized.

210
00:08:48,955 --> 00:08:50,220
Mom will surely be heartbroken

211
00:08:50,220 --> 00:08:51,500
if she sees you like this.

212
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:55,220
Keep them, then.

213
00:08:56,466 --> 00:08:57,980
I didn't forbid you from doing it.

214
00:09:00,290 --> 00:09:01,620
She's already gone.

215
00:09:03,620 --> 00:09:05,020
Her items remind me of her.

216
00:09:06,220 --> 00:09:06,980
They torment me.

217
00:09:07,570 --> 00:09:08,170
Lina!

218
00:09:08,930 --> 00:09:09,740
Lina!

219
00:09:12,930 --> 00:09:13,340
Mom.

220
00:09:13,422 --> 00:09:14,260
So, your unit is here.

221
00:09:14,260 --> 00:09:15,340
- It's here.
- Give it to me.

222
00:09:15,340 --> 00:09:16,000
Hold this for me.

223
00:09:16,170 --> 00:09:16,890
It's so heavy.

224
00:09:17,740 --> 00:09:18,340
Grandma.

225
00:09:18,377 --> 00:09:20,190
You're at home?
Is it not time for school yet?

226
00:09:20,690 --> 00:09:21,260
Look.

227
00:09:21,288 --> 00:09:23,170
Look at the giant fish
your grandpa had caught.

228
00:09:23,170 --> 00:09:23,770
It's huge.

229
00:09:24,100 --> 00:09:24,460
Look.

230
00:09:24,460 --> 00:09:25,230
Grandpa is amazing.

231
00:09:25,260 --> 00:09:25,890
Yeah, right?

232
00:09:26,020 --> 00:09:28,050
Mom, I have to send Duole to school.

233
00:09:28,050 --> 00:09:28,760
I'm running late.

234
00:09:28,930 --> 00:09:29,460
Okay.

235
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:30,577
Please enjoy the breakfast.

236
00:09:30,740 --> 00:09:31,570
Okay. Go ahead.

237
00:09:31,860 --> 00:09:32,340
Take care.

238
00:09:32,340 --> 00:09:33,020
Goodbye, Grandma.

239
00:09:33,020 --> 00:09:33,690
Alright.

240
00:09:33,822 --> 00:09:34,844
Have you had breakfast?

241
00:09:34,890 --> 00:09:35,570
I have.

242
00:09:37,980 --> 00:09:38,530
In-law.

243
00:09:38,810 --> 00:09:39,530
Listen.

244
00:09:39,690 --> 00:09:41,260
My husband caught a huge fish.

245
00:09:41,333 --> 00:09:42,377
He said it was for you...

246
00:09:50,930 --> 00:09:52,100
He's asleep.

247
00:09:52,930 --> 00:09:53,570
Is he?

248
00:09:55,460 --> 00:09:56,890
What's with the music?

249
00:09:56,890 --> 00:09:58,260
It chills the heart.

250
00:09:59,890 --> 00:10:01,190
Mom, he finally agreed to let me

251
00:10:01,190 --> 00:10:02,530
organize my mother-in-law's items.

252
00:10:02,530 --> 00:10:03,620
Lend me a hand later.

253
00:10:03,980 --> 00:10:05,930
You should've done that long ago.

254
00:10:06,410 --> 00:10:07,260
I waited until now.

255
00:10:09,977 --> 00:10:11,050
It looks good on me, right?

256
00:10:11,170 --> 00:10:12,140
Isn't it hot?

257
00:10:16,650 --> 00:10:17,650
This coat is pretty nice.

258
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:19,410
The fabric is great.

259
00:10:19,711 --> 00:10:21,111
The color is vibrant as well.

260
00:10:23,170 --> 00:10:23,740
Listen.

261
00:10:23,900 --> 00:10:24,980
I'll take it with me later.

262
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:26,355
Don't even think about it.

263
00:10:26,622 --> 00:10:28,530
Shen Dai bought this coat
with her scholarship.

264
00:10:28,650 --> 00:10:30,640
She told me to mail it to the U.S.

265
00:10:30,644 --> 00:10:31,500
before she left.

266
00:10:34,444 --> 00:10:36,260
Your sister-in-law
is kind of troublesome.

267
00:10:36,422 --> 00:10:37,949
She wants you to mail it to the U.S.?

268
00:10:37,950 --> 00:10:39,880
Do you know how much
the shipping fee will cost?

269
00:10:40,222 --> 00:10:41,644
I'll ask her to do cash on delivery.

270
00:10:41,933 --> 00:10:42,740
Cash on delivery?

271
00:10:43,088 --> 00:10:43,822
Take it with you.

272
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:45,355
Take all of them with you.

273
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:47,911
I can't take any of them.

274
00:10:48,511 --> 00:10:48,930
Here.

275
00:10:48,930 --> 00:10:49,288
This...

276
00:10:49,311 --> 00:10:50,177
Open the trash bag.

277
00:10:50,410 --> 00:10:50,980
The cookies...

278
00:10:51,300 --> 00:10:52,500
They're still sealed, you know?

279
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:53,450
All of them are expired.

280
00:10:53,450 --> 00:10:54,400
I've checked all of them.

281
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:55,109
Open the trash bag.

282
00:10:55,110 --> 00:10:58,080
Your mother-in-law was too particular.
That's why she passed away early.

283
00:10:58,170 --> 00:11:00,020
Your father and I ate everything we had.

284
00:11:00,020 --> 00:11:01,500
Look. We're still jumping around.

285
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:02,690
They're no longer edible.

286
00:11:03,244 --> 00:11:04,888
Medical fees are
much more expensive.

287
00:11:04,933 --> 00:11:05,311
Come.

288
00:11:06,140 --> 00:11:06,500
Fine.

289
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:08,100
Here. Quickly.

290
00:11:08,100 --> 00:11:09,220
Put all of them in the bag.

